  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.240" end="00:00:05.540" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visors, and welcome to your first
<br />base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:05.540" end="00:00:07.220" tts:direction="ltr">With all base camps,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:07.220" end="00:00:09.999" tts:direction="ltr">I like to lead with a guiding question
<br />that</p>
        <p begin="00:00:09.999" end="00:00:13.579" tts:direction="ltr">you will be able to answer at the end of
<br />the base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:13.579" end="00:00:16.720" tts:direction="ltr">This one is, can you communicate</p>
        <p begin="00:00:16.720" end="00:00:20.459" tts:direction="ltr">the right data to the right audience in
<br />the right way?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.459" end="00:00:22.759" tts:direction="ltr">Let's jump right in.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.759" end="00:00:26.760" tts:direction="ltr">You will have four different base camps
<br />throughout this course.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.760" end="00:00:28.819" tts:direction="ltr">As I mentioned, this is the first one,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:28.819" end="00:00:31.650" tts:direction="ltr">and this one will focus on PEC.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:31.650" end="00:00:36.299" tts:direction="ltr">PAC. It's the acronym that I'm using for
<br />purpose,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:36.299" end="00:00:39.900" tts:direction="ltr">audience, and credibility and has that
<br />guiding question.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:39.900" end="00:00:43.599" tts:direction="ltr">You'll see that the K in PAC will be part
<br />of</p>
        <p begin="00:00:43.599" end="00:00:48.539" tts:direction="ltr">the base camp number two and we'll cover
<br />different chart kinds.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:48.539" end="00:00:52.239" tts:direction="ltr">Let's take a look at our rubric because
<br />it's</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.239" end="00:00:55.519" tts:direction="ltr">important for you to know that as we're
<br />going on this journey,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:55.519" end="00:00:58.239" tts:direction="ltr">we are also going to be building the
<br />rubric</p>
        <p begin="00:00:58.239" end="00:01:01.440" tts:direction="ltr">that will be used in your final project.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:01.440" end="00:01:04.080" tts:direction="ltr">We're going to start off with our PAC,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:04.080" end="00:01:08.359" tts:direction="ltr">our PAC, we'll do our K and our next base
<br />camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:08.359" end="00:01:12.520" tts:direction="ltr">But you'll see here that We have the
<br />purpose,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:12.520" end="00:01:17.539" tts:direction="ltr">audience and credibility and the
<br />expectations you have for those three
<br />items.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:17.539" end="00:01:22.079" tts:direction="ltr">Then we'll move on to design and we'll end
<br />with story.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:22.079" end="00:01:24.979" tts:direction="ltr">As I mentioned before, with our pack,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:24.979" end="00:01:28.160" tts:direction="ltr">we're going to focus on those primarily so
<br />that you can</p>
        <p begin="00:01:28.160" end="00:01:32.539" tts:direction="ltr">really hone in on purpose, audience and
<br />credibility.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:32.539" end="00:01:39.140" tts:direction="ltr">Let's start our first base camp with this
<br />concept of journey and purpose.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:39.140" end="00:01:43.159" tts:direction="ltr">Whenever you're about to go on an
<br />adventure,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:43.159" end="00:01:48.919" tts:direction="ltr">you typically pack something to bring with
